Preheat grill for medium heat and lightly oil grate. In a large bowl, mix the lamb, mint, oregano, garlic, cumin, allspice, salt and pepper. Divide meat and shape into 4 patties. Place patties on grill. Cover and cook turning once, until burgers are well seared, or temperature reads 160 degrees F (70 degrees C) about 8 minutes for medium-well.